    <h2 id="section-1">1. General</h2>

    <details>
        <summary>What is WetWijzer?</summary>
        <div>
            <p>WetWijzer is an unofficial search and information platform for Belgian legislation. It offers searchable databases of laws, decrees, ordinances, case law and parliamentary documents, supplemented by an AI chatbot that answers questions about Belgian law.</p>
            <p>The service is also available as <a href="https://lisloi.be">LisLoi</a> (French) and <a href="https://gesetzguide.be">GesetzGuide</a> (German) and <a href="https://lexlibera.be">LexLibera</a> (English).</p>
        </div>
    </details>

    <details>
        <summary>Is WetWijzer an official government initiative?</summary>
        <div><p>No. WetWijzer is independent of the Belgian government, the judiciary, the Belgian Bar Associations and all other official bodies. The information on the platform originates from public sources such as the Belgian Official Gazette, Justel, Reflex, JuPortal and EUR-Lex.</p></div>
    </details>

    <details>
        <summary>Is the information on WetWijzer legal advice?</summary>
        <div><p><strong>No.</strong> All information on WetWijzer, including responses from the AI chatbot, is provided for general informational purposes only. No attorney-client relationship is created. Always consult a qualified lawyer for your specific situation.</p></div>
    </details>

    <details>
        <summary>Is WetWijzer free to use?</summary>
        <div><p>Searching the legislation database is entirely free and requires no account. Visitors from Belgium can also ask <strong>3 free chatbot questions per week</strong> without registration (⚡ Smart level only, legislation only). With a free account, you receive 3 credits per week with additional intelligence levels. Additional credits can be purchased, or you can subscribe to WetWijzer Pro for extended functionality.</p></div>
    </details>

    <details>
        <summary>In which languages is WetWijzer available?</summary>
        <div><p>The interface is available in Dutch, French, German and English. The AI chatbot responds in the language you select. The legislation database contains texts in their original publication language.</p></div>
    </details>

    <h2 id="section-2">2. Account and registration</h2>

    <details>
        <summary>Do I need an account?</summary>
        <div>
            <p>Searching the legislation database does not require an account. The AI chatbot is also <strong>available in limited form without an account</strong> for Belgian visitors (up to 3 questions per week, ⚡ Smart level only, legislation only). An account is needed to:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Use higher intelligence levels (⭐ Genius and above)</li>
                <li>Purchase credits</li>
                <li>Subscribe to WetWijzer Pro</li>
                <li>Save bookmarks</li>
                <li>Permanently store preferences</li>
                <li>Save conversations to your profile</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </details>

    <details>
        <summary>What information is required for registration?</summary>
        <div><p>Only an email address and password. Your name is optional. We do not ask for phone number, address or any other personal data.</p></div>
    </details>

    <details>
        <summary>How do I delete my account?</summary>
        <div>
            <p>You can delete your account via the account page. After confirmation, your account will be scheduled for permanent deletion after 30 days. During this period, you can contact us to cancel the deletion. After 30 days, all personal data is irreversibly erased.</p>
            <p>Unused credits are not refunded upon deletion.</p>
        </div>
    </details>

    <details>
        <summary>What happens if I do not confirm my email?</summary>
        <div><p>Unconfirmed accounts are automatically deleted after 72 hours. You can re-register afterwards.</p></div>
    </details>

    <h2 id="section-3">3. AI chatbot</h2>

    <details>
        <summary>How does the AI chatbot work?</summary>
        <div>
            <p>The chatbot uses Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG): your question is first matched against the Belgian legislation database to find relevant legal articles, then a large language model (LLM) formulates a response based on those sources.</p>
            <p>This improves accuracy compared to a standard chatbot, but does not eliminate all risks of inaccuracy.</p>
        </div>
    </details>

    <details>
        <summary>What are the intelligence levels?</summary>
        <div>
            <table>
                <tr><th>Level</th><th>Credits</th><th>Default model</th><th>Suited for</th><th>Access</th></tr>
                <tr><td>⚡ Smart</td><td>1</td><td>GPT-5 Mini / Mistral Small</td><td>Quick lookups</td><td>Free</td></tr>
                <tr><td>⭐ Genius</td><td>3</td><td>o4-mini / Claude 4.5 Haiku</td><td>In-depth legal analysis</td><td>Pro only ⭐ Recommended</td></tr>
                <tr><td>🏆 Mastermind</td><td>5</td><td>GPT-5 / Claude Sonnet 4 / GPT-5.4</td><td>Maximum accuracy</td><td>Pro only</td></tr>
                <tr><td>🔮 Omniscient</td><td>10</td><td>Claude Opus 4 / GPT-5.5</td><td>Unique perspective, premium analysis</td><td>Pro only</td></tr>
            </table>
            <p>Free users receive 3 credits per week for ⚡ Smart. ⭐ Genius, 🏆 Mastermind and 🔮 Omniscient are exclusive to Pro subscribers.</p>
        </div>
    </details>

    <details>
        <summary>How is reasoning depth determined?</summary>
        <div>
            <p>Reasoning depth is automatically built into each intelligence level — you don't need to configure anything. Each level uses the optimal reasoning setting for its model:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Smart:</strong> quick thinking (smaller models perform better without deep reasoning)</li>
                <li><strong>Genius:</strong> balanced thinking (o4-mini and Claude 4.5 Haiku perform optimally at this level)</li>
                <li><strong>Mastermind:</strong> balanced thinking (GPT-5 and Claude Sonnet 4 perform optimally at this level)</li>
                <li><strong>Omniscient:</strong> Claude Opus 4 and GPT-5.5 always operate at maximum capacity</li>
            </ul>
            <p>There are <strong>no extra credits</strong> for reasoning depth — costs are fully included in the per-level credit price.</p>
        </div>
    </details>

    <details>
        <summary>Can I trust the chatbot responses?</summary>
        <div>
            <p><strong>No, not without verification.</strong> The AI chatbot may:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Present incorrect information as fact ("hallucinations")</li>
                <li>Cite outdated legislation</li>
                <li>Misinterpret legal concepts</li>
                <li>Reference non-existent laws or articles</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Always verify responses against official sources or consult a legal professional. The brilliant level generally provides more accurate answers than the simple level.</p>
        </div>
    </details>

    <details>
        <summary>What is the difference between the chatbot and Google?</summary>
        <div>
            <p>The WetWijzer chatbot is specifically connected to the Belgian legislation database. Unlike a generic search engine:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>The chatbot searches the full text of Belgian laws, decrees and ordinances directly</li>
                <li>The chatbot cites specific legal articles with source references</li>
                <li>The chatbot formulates a coherent answer instead of a list of links</li>
                <li>Anyone can search the case law database, and Pro users can additionally search parliamentary documents</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </details>

    <details>
        <summary>Are my chatbot conversations stored?</summary>
        <div>
            <p><strong>Only on our server, and only if you are logged in.</strong> For logged-in users, conversations are stored encrypted (AES-256) on our server. For non-logged-in visitors, conversations are held exclusively in your browser's working memory — they disappear as soon as you leave the page or close your browser. <strong>No localStorage, sessionStorage or other browser persistence</strong> is used.</p>
            <p>Our analytics database records exclusively metadata (legal domain, language, intelligence level, credits) — never the content of your questions.</p>
            <p>See our <a href="/privacy-policy">privacy policy (section 3.4)</a> for full details.</p>
        </div>
    </details>

    <details>
        <summary>Where are my questions processed?</summary>
        <div><p><strong>All AI models</strong> process your questions within the EU. OpenAI models (GPT-5 Mini, GPT-5.4, GPT-5, GPT-5.5, o4-mini) run on Azure OpenAI in Sweden Central (Sweden). Claude models (Opus 4, 4.5 Haiku, 3.5 Sonnet) run on Azure AI Services and AWS Bedrock, also within the EU. All processing remains within the EU/EEA.</p></div>
    </details>

