    <h2 id="section-9">9. Technical</h2>

    <details>
        <summary>Is WetWijzer open source?</summary>
        <div><p>Yes. The source code is available on <a href="https://github.com/WetWijzer-LisLoi/WetWijzer">GitHub</a> under the MIT licence. Anyone can view, verify and contribute to the code.</p></div>
    </details>

    <details>
        <summary>Which browsers are supported?</summary>
        <div><p>WetWijzer works in all modern browsers: Chrome, Firefox, Safari and Edge. Internet Explorer is not supported.</p></div>
    </details>

    <details>
        <summary>What is the relationship with Praxis Legal?</summary>
        <div><p>Praxis Legal Practice Suite is a desktop application for law firms. Praxis users can link their account to WetWijzer for SSO authentication and shared credit management. Both services are managed by the same data controller. The integration is optional and available to Pro subscribers.</p></div>
    </details>

    <details>
        <summary>How current is the legislation database?</summary>
        <div><p>The database is regularly updated based on the Belgian Official Gazette and other official sources. We strive for currency but cannot guarantee that all texts contain the most recent consolidated version. When in doubt, always check the official publication via <a href="https://www.ejustice.just.fgov.be">Justel</a>.</p></div>
    </details>

